response.value:
The `__exidx_end` is not a section, but a symbol defined in the linker script. It's used to mark the end of the `.ARM.exidx` section, which is a special section used by the ARM compiler.

The `.ARM.exidx` section is used for exception handling in ARM architecture. It contains a table of function exception handling information. The `__exidx_start` and `__exidx_end` symbols are used to denote the start and end of this section, respectively.

These symbols can be used in your code to determine the size of the `.ARM.exidx` section or to iterate over the entries in the exception index table. For example, you might see code like this in an ARM-based embedded system:

```c
extern void *__exidx_start;
extern void *__exidx_end;

void process_exidx_table() {
    void *p = &__exidx_start;
    while (p < &__exidx_end) {
        // Process each entry in the table
        p++;
    }
}
```

This code would iterate over each entry in the `.ARM.exidx` section and process it in some way. The exact details of how to process the entries would depend on the specifics of your application.

